title: The World I love to see (Photography Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Pdf / English / 1981 / 135 pages / 24 MB

"I had left Germany on the Bremen with my sister's red scarf waving until I watered it out of focus. I was young enough in 1964 to dare the venture alone, and mature enough to make it work. Photography had been my hobby, and it became my life.
When I came to America, a new and different world, I learned to see. So much intrigued my eye. I photographed everything that seemed friendly and fresh: interesting designs, fire escapes, shapes, people's faces with long eyelashes, the sea. Every day held a discovery."

Ulrike Welsch, 1981
